mongodb is a document database,it is of keys and values
it is a nosql database
we can perform crud operations with it
c-create
r-read
u-update
d-delete

create-
showdbs-it will listout all the databases
use dbname- we can change oe create a newdatabase by using the keyword use
collection-it is like a folder, to create it
db.createCollection("posts")-so it creates the collectionnof posts
there are two ways to insert data-insertOneinsertMany
db.posts.insertOne({name:"praneeth,age:22})
it will insert one document
db.posts,insertMany([{name:"praneeth",age:22},{name:"surya",age:22}])
it will insert array of documents

read-
db.posts.find() it will list out all the documents in the posts
db.posts.findOne() it will list out one document
db.posts.find({name:"praneeth"}) it will list out the values with the name praneeth
db.posts.find({},{name:1}) it will give name with objectid
db.posts.find({},{name:1,_id:0}) it will give only name without objectid

update-to update the documents, there are 2 ways-updateOne,updateMany
db.posts.updateOne({name:"praneeth"},{$set:{age:23}}) it will update the age of praneeth to 23
db.posts.updateMany({},{$inc:{age:1}})

delete-there are two types, deleteOne,deleteMany
db.posts.deleteOne({name:"praneeth"}) it will delete the document with name praneeth
db.posts.deleteMany({}) it will delete all the documents